---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="DMCA / Copyright Policy"
  description="MCLA's Digital Millennium Copyright Act (DMCA) policy and process for reporting copyright infringement."
  noindex={true}
>
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-warm-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold text-text-dark tracking-[-0.5px] mb-6">Digital Millennium Copyright Act (DMCA) Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-text-light text-sm mb-12">Effective April 15, 2026</p>

      <div class="prose max-w-none">
        <p class="text-text-mid">
          The Mantle Cell Lymphoma Alliance respects intellectual property rights and expects users to do the same.
        </p>

        <h2>To Report Infringement</h2>
        <p class="text-text-mid">
          If you believe content on our site infringes your copyright, please provide our designated agent with:
        </p>
        <ul class="text-text-mid">
          <li>Your contact information (name, address, phone, email)</li>
          <li>Description of the copyrighted work allegedly infringed</li>
          <li>Specific location (URL) of the material on our site</li>
          <li>Statement of good faith belief that use is unauthorized</li>
          <li>Statement that notice information is accurate, and under penalty of perjury, that you are the copyright owner or authorized agent</li>
          <li>Your physical or electronic signature</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Designated Agent</h2>
        <p class="text-text-mid">
          Karen Holden<br />
          Email: <a href="mailto:karen@mantlecellalliance.org">karen@mantlecellalliance.org</a>
        </p>

        <h2>Our Response</h2>
        <p class="text-text-mid">
          Upon receiving a valid notice, we will promptly review and, if appropriate, remove or disable access to the material.
        </p>

        <h2>Counter-Notification</h2>
        <p class="text-text-mid">
          If you believe material was removed in error, you may submit a counter-notification including:
        </p>
        <ul class="text-text-mid">
          <li>Your contact information</li>
          <li>Identification of removed material and its prior location</li>
          <li>Statement under penalty of perjury that removal was mistaken</li>
          <li>Consent to federal court jurisdiction</li>
          <li>Your signature</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Repeat Infringers</h2>
        <p class="text-text-mid">
          We reserve the right to terminate access for users determined to be repeat infringers.
        </p>

        <h2>Policy Updates</h2>
        <p class="text-text-mid">
          This policy may be revised; updates will be posted here with a new effective date.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
